Anthony S. Chapman

*********************************************
*********** Section 1 Contents **************
*********************************************
The folder 'executables' contains two executable files, one for Windows (called 'portOptWin.exe') and one for Unix/Linux (called 'portOptUnix') systems. It also has an example asset file (called 'assetTest.txt').

The folder 'source' contains the source files. 'PSO.hs' is the module that deals with the main PSO algorithm. 'portOpt.hs' deals with that actual portfolio optimisation function. 

*********************************************
********* Section 2 Dependancies ************
*********************************************
The Haskell Platform can be downloaded and installed from 'http://www.haskell.org/platform/'. 

*********************************************
********** Section 3 Compiling **************
*********************************************
To compile 'portOpt.hs'
	1) Open a terminal or command line
	2) Move to the forlder containing the source files
	3) Type into the terminal the following command and press enter:
		ghc --make portOpt.hs
	4) You how now created an executable file called 'portOpt' in Unix/Linux or 'portOpt.exe' in Windows.

*********************************************
*********** Section 4 Running ***************
*********************************************
Running the program in Windows:
	1) Open a folder
	2) Move to where the executable file is
	3) Double click on the executable file
	4) A new window should open with further instructions.

Running the program in Unix/Linux:
	1) Open a terminal
	2) Move to the forlder containing the executabl file
	3) Type into the terminal the following command and press enter:
		./portOptUnix or ./portOpt

For further instructions please refer to the User Manual.
